com.clarionmedia.infinitum.orm

Class LazyLoadDexMakerProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.clarionmedia.infinitum.di.AbstractProxy
      • com.clarionmedia.infinitum.di.DexMakerProxy
        • com.clarionmedia.infinitum.orm.LazyLoadDexMakerProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.reflect.InvocationHandler

    public abstract class LazyLoadDexMakerProxy
extends DexMakerProxy

    Used to proxy an Object which has been configured to lazily load. Every method called on the Object will pass through this InvocationHandler. This handler is responsible for lazily loading the Object, which occurs in loadObject().

    The first method invocation made on a proxy will result in the proxied Object being loaded and then the method will be passed to the loaded Object for invocation. Any subsequent method invocation made on the proxy will simply be intercepted and propagated to the Object.
